text.section:
Any designation of an alternate may, at the appointing member's direction:
Be limited upon the face of the appointing instrument to be effective only for a designated meeting or only for specified business;
Be shown on the face of the appointing instrument to be on a continuing basis, but in no case for a period of more than four (4) years, whenever the appointing member is unable to attend;
Be revoked by the appointing member in an instrument of like formality, similarly filed with the secretary as a public record of the commission.
